The paper discusses the challenges and approaches for performing machine learning on structured data, which is a topic that spans across multiple sub-fields of computer science. However, given the focus on representation learning and embeddings, it is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of convolutional and recurrent neural networks suggests relevance to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of metric learning and graph convolutional neural networks suggests relevance to cs.DB (Databases) sub-category.
